bit_field.name: SWIDTH
bit_field.description: SWIDTH[N] represents a trace port width of (N+1). The meaning of each bit is: 0 = Width (N+1) not supported. 1 = Width (N+1) supported.

bit_field.name: CWIDTH
bit_field.description: CWIDTH[N] represents a trace port width of (N+1). The meaning of each bit is: 0 = Width (N+1) is not the current trace port width. 1 = Width (N+1) is the current trace port width.

bit_field.name: PRESCALER
bit_field.description: Divisor for TRACECLKIN is Prescaler + 1

bit_field.name: TXMODE
bit_field.description: Specified the protocol for trace output from the TPIU.

bit_field_value.name: SPPR_TXMODE_0b11
bit_field_value.description: Reserved. The effect of selecting a reserved value, or a mode that the implementation does not support, is UNPREDICTABLE.

bit_field.name: F1InProg
bit_field.description: F1InProg. This bit always reads zero

bit_field.name: FtStopped
bit_field.description: FtStopped. This bit always reads zero

bit_field.name: TCPresent
bit_field.description: TCPresent. This bit always reads zero

bit_field.name: FtNonStop
bit_field.description: FtNonStop. Formatter cannot be stopped

bit_field.name: EnFCont
bit_field.description: Enable continuous formatting.

bit_field.name: TrigIn
bit_field.description: This bit Reads-As-One (RAO), specifying that triggers are inserted when a trigger pin is asserted.

bit_field.name: CycCount
bit_field.description: CycCount[11:0]. 12-bit counter value to indicate the number of complete frames between full synchronization packets. Default value is 64 (0x40).

bit_field.name: TRIGGER
bit_field.description: TRIGGER input value. When read, this bit returns the TRIGGER input.

bit_field.name: ETMdata0
bit_field.description: ETM trace data. The TPIU discards this data when the registers is read.

bit_field.name: ETMdata1
bit_field.description: ETM trace data. The TPIU discards this data when the registers is read.

bit_field.name: ETMdata2
bit_field.description: ETM trace data. The TPIU discards this data when the registers is read.

bit_field.name: ETMbytecount
bit_field.description: Number of bytes of ETM trace data since last read of Integration ETM Data Register.

bit_field.name: ETMATVALID
bit_field.description: Returns the value of the ETM ATVALID signal.

bit_field.name: ITMbytecount
bit_field.description: Number of bytes of ITM trace data since last read of Integration ITM Data Register.

bit_field.name: ITMATVALID
bit_field.description: Returns the value of the ITM ATVALID signal.

bit_field.name: ATREADY1_ATREADY2
bit_field.description: This bit sets the value of both the ETM and ITM ATREADY.

bit_field.name: ATVALID1_ATVALID2
bit_field.description: A read of this bit returns the value of ATVALIDS1 OR-ed with ATVALIDS2.

bit_field.name: ITMdata0
bit_field.description: ITM trace data. The TPIU discards this data when the registers is read.

bit_field.name: ITMdata1
bit_field.description: ITM trace data. The TPIU discards this data when the registers is read.

bit_field.name: ITMdata2
bit_field.description: ITM trace data. The TPIU discards this data when the registers is read.

bit_field.name: ETMbytecount
bit_field.description: Number of bytes of ETM trace data since last read of Integration ETM Data Register.

bit_field.name: ETMATVALID
bit_field.description: Returns the value of the ETM ATVALID signal.

bit_field.name: ITMbytecount
bit_field.description: Number of bytes of ITM trace data since last read of Integration ITM Data Register.

bit_field.name: ITMATVALID
bit_field.description: Returns the value of the ITM ATVALID signal.

bit_field.name: Mode
bit_field.description: Specifies the current mode for the TPIU.

bit_field.name: CLAIMSET
bit_field.description: A bit programmable register bank which sets the Claim Tag Value. Write 1 to set the bit in the claim tag. A read will return a logic 1 for all implemented locations.

bit_field.name: CLAIMCLR
bit_field.description: A bit programmable register bank that is zero at reset. Write 1 to clear the bit in the claim tag. On reads, returns the current setting of the claim tag.

bit_field.name: NumberOfTraceInputs
bit_field.description: Number of trace inputs. Specifies the number of trace inputs: b000000 = 1 input b000001 = 2 inputs If your implementation includes an ETM, the value of this field is b000001.

bit_field.name: TRACECELKIN
bit_field.description: Asynchronous TRACECLKIN. Specifies whether TRACECLKIN can be asynchronous to CLK.

bit_field_value.name: DEVID_TRACECELKIN_0b0
bit_field_value.description: b0 = TRACECLKIN must be synchronous to CLK

bit_field_value.name: DEVID_TRACECELKIN_0b1
bit_field_value.description: b1 = TRACECLKIN can be asynchronous to CLK

bit_field.name: MinimumBufferSize
bit_field.description: Minimum buffer size. Specifies the minimum TPIU buffer size: b010 = 4 bytes

bit_field.name: TraceAndClockModes
bit_field.description: Trace and clock modes. This bit Reads-As-Zero (RAZ), indicating that tracedata and clock modes are supported.

bit_field.name: Manchester
bit_field.description: Asynchronous Serial Wire Output (Manchester). This bit Reads-As-One (RAO), indicating that the output is supported.

bit_field.name: NRZ
bit_field.description: Asynchronous Serial Wire Output (NRZ). This bit Reads-As-One (RAO), indicating that the output is supported.
